modules.description: Handles message formatting and parsing for syslog protocol, including facility, severity, and timestamp extraction. Operates on strings, tuples representing log levels, and custom record types for log entries. Used to process incoming syslog messages from network sources and prepare them for storage or forwarding.

Provides functions to parse syslog facilities from strings, open a syslog connection with specified parameters, send log messages with a given level, and close the connection. Works with facility, flag, level, and t types representing syslog configuration and state. Used to integrate application logging with system syslog services, ensuring messages are categorized and routed appropriately.
